# --- README.md ---
# Expo Todo App (SDK‑54) + FastAPI Backend

This repository contains a **full‑stack** Todo application built for beginners:

- **Backend** – FastAPI (Python 3.12+) exposing `/health`, `/todos` (GET) and `/todos` (POST).
- **Frontend** – Expo SDK‑54 React Native app that displays the Todo list and lets you add new items.

## How to run
```bash
# Clone the repo and cd into it
git clone <repo-url>
cd expo-todo

# ---------- Backend ----------
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate   # on Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install .
uvicorn src.main:app --reload   # server runs on http://127.0.0.1:8000

# Run tests
pytest -q

# ---------- Frontend (Expo) ----------
cd expo_app
npm install               # installs expo, react-native, axios, etc.
npm start                  # shows QR code for Expo Go
```

Open the QR code with the Expo Go app on your phone (or an emulator) and you’ll see the Todo list UI.

